<COREF ID="3" TYPE="IDENT">These</COREF> served as money charms for <COREF ID="32" TYPE="IDENT">shops , whose <COREF ID="46" TYPE="IDENT">owners</COREF> would turn <COREF ID="3" TYPE="IDENT">them</COREF> facing outward in the morning so as to attract wealth inside</COREF> .
